## What the test suite covers

| Category | Test class | Key assertions |
|---|---|---|
| **Accepted formats** | `TestAcceptedFormats` | PDF, PNG, JPG/JPEG all return `status == "created"` with a non-empty `document_id` |
| **Rejected formats** | `TestRejectedFormats` | 10 disallowed MIME types are parametrised; mismatched extension/MIME also rejected; rejection message is non-empty |
| **File-size boundaries** | `TestFileSizeLimits` | Exactly 10 MB ✅, 10 MB + 1 byte ❌, empty file ❌; BVA at 1, 3, 5, 7, 9 MB |
| **Idempotency – explicit key** | `TestIdempotency` | Same key → same `document_id`; status is `already_exists`; 3 retries produce one record |
| **Idempotency – content hash** | `TestIdempotency` | Duplicate content without a key → same `document_id` |
| **Idempotency – transient failure** | `TestIdempotency` | Network error on attempt 1, retry on attempt 2 → accepted, no duplicate |
| **Rejected calls not memoised** | `TestIdempotency` | A previously-rejected idempotency key must not block a corrected retry |
| **Cross-cutting edge cases** | `TestCombinedEdgeCases` | Oversized/invalid format still rejected with a key; multi-employee uploads; uppercase extensions handled gracefully |
